Package: RobustMediate
Title: Causal Mediation Analysis with Diagnostics and Sensitivity Analysis
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Subir", "Hait", , "haitsubi@msu.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0009-0004-9871-9677"))
Description: Provides tools for causal mediation analysis with continuous
    treatments using inverse probability weighting (IPW). Estimates natural
    direct and indirect effects over a user-defined treatment grid and includes
    diagnostic and sensitivity analysis procedures. Balance diagnostics are
    provided for both treatment and mediator models using standardized mean
    differences. The package implements pathway-specific extensions of the
    impact threshold for a confounding variable (ITCV; Frank, 2000) for
    mediation settings, along with joint visualization of E-values
    (VanderWeele and Ding, 2017) and sequential ignorability violations
    (Imai et al., 2010). Additional utilities include visualization of
    dose-response mediation functions and formatted diagnostic summaries
    for applied analyses. Supports clustered data and multiple outcome families. References: Frank (2000) <doi:10.1177/0049124100029002002>; VanderWeele and Ding (2017) <doi:10.7326/M16-2607>; Imai, Keele, and Yamamoto (2010) <doi:10.1214/10-STS321>.
